#note a tough, tough position. I wasn't sure whether I should play a one tile play or try to defend. in a sense quackle won't really help because his last play demonstrates that he doesn't have a random rack, but more likely something powerful...in the end,  I think this is the right play. I analyzed the position in depth and he bingoes 10/36 times (10/28 assuming he has the blank after VUM). of course that's skewed by an analysis of what he had last turn, but the trouble is that I can't outrun bingos with a long play, and a one-tile play (presumably dropping the M for 14) leaves me with the V, which will kill my chances of responding with a winning counterplay. So, in the end - I think this is right, but my chances aren't great...
